description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chippenham Stroke Unit ( Fixed Term - maternity cover)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Specialist SLT  – 0.6 WTE (22.5 Hours per Week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;  (experienced Band 5 applicants would also be considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Band 6 (or experienced Band 5) Speech and Language Therapist  to work on the 20 bedded Stroke Unit based at Chippenham Hospital. This would be to provide maternity cover from 30.11.20 until mid-May 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to provide clear evidence of up to date and relevant clinical practice and education as well as an appetite for innovative practice. Applicants need to have enthusiasm and commitment to working within a stroke based team and to have recent experience of working in or in partnership with stroke services within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialist knowledge of stroke is essential, as is post graduate dysphagia training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an extremely friendly and supportive Department which has an excellent system of supervision and mentoring.  Where are opportunities for CPD and we run a regular Journal Club.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post provides an exciting opportunity to develop specialist skills within our small team, as there will be opportunities  to support less experienced colleagues and work directly with an SLT Assistant on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A car owner/driver is useful but not essential and you will need to be a member of the RCSLT and HCPC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcome to  Sam Dicks, Head of SLT Service  on 07900 497181&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;s.dicks@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
